T1  - Maximum likelihood estimation of stochastic frontier production models
AU  - Greene, William H.
JO  - Journal of Econometrics
VL  - 18
IS  - 2
SP  - 285
EP  - 289
PY  - 1982
DA  - 1982/02/01/
SN  - 0304-4076
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0304-4076(82)90043-4
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0304407682900434
AB  - In his 1977 paper on the Tobit model, Fair devised a procedure for maximum likelihood estimation which greatly simplified the process. The procedure, in fact, can be generalized to encompass a wide variety of limited dependent variable models, as is demonstrated in Greene (1981). In this note, we show how Fair's method can be extended to the frontier production model. The algorithm is surprisingly simple to implement and, in our experience, can result in substantial reductions in cost.
